  "content_en": "<div class=\"royal-legacy-card\"><div class=\"legacy-section\"><div class=\"legacy-section-header\"><span class=\"legacy-icon\"> üëë</span><h5>Golden Age of the Yadava Dynasty</h5></div><div class=\"legacy-section-content\"><p>Singhana II was the most powerful ruler of the Yadava dynasty. He expanded the empire by defeating the Hoysalas, Kakatiyas, and Shilaharas. His empire stretched from Malwa in the north to the Kaveri in the south.</p></div></div><div class=\"legacy-section\"><div class=\"legacy-section-header\"><span class=\"legacy-icon\"> üéµ</span><h5>Music and Astronomy</h5></div><div class=\"legacy-section-content\"><p>He was a great patron of arts and sciences. His courtier <strong>Sharangadeva</strong> wrote the famous treatise <strong>'Sangeet Ratnakara'</strong> on Indian classical music. Changadeva, the grandson of the great mathematician and astronomer Bhaskara II (Bhaskaracharya), was also in his court, who founded a college for the study of astronomy.</p></div></div></div>"
